WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:29.774
- Sí. Bueno.
-  Family is everything.

3
00:02:29.899 --> 00:02:31.693
No?

4
00:02:31.776 --> 00:02:35.196
Now. do you love your son?

5
00:02:36.156 --> 00:02:39.909
Sí.

6
00:02:46.791 --> 00:02:51.379
Now... do you understand?

7
00:02:51.504 --> 00:02:55.884
You have a $10 million insurance policy.
I know that.

8
00:05:05.388 --> 00:05:07.515
Georgina!

9
00:05:07.599 --> 00:05:10.894
Obey me. I will love you.
Come on.

10
00:05:10.977 --> 00:05:12.729
That's how it works. huh?

11
00:05:12.854 --> 00:05:16.024
- Simple.
- That's right.

12
00:05:16.107 --> 00:05:18.026
Mwah.

13
00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:25.450
She got a sister?

14
00:05:25.575 --> 00:05:28.745
How's business?

15
00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:31.748
The Japanese are here in a big way.

16
00:05:33.208 --> 00:05:35.710
Cheap labor. factory space.

17
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:39.756
But they feel a lot safer living
over the border in El Paso.

18
00:05:39.881 --> 00:05:42.926
I ferry them back and forth.
They think I'm John Wayne.

19
00:05:43.051 --> 00:05:44.928
- Ah.
- Come on.

20
00:05:49.432 --> 00:05:52.644
- I live like a king down here.
- Yes. you do.

21
00:05:56.398 --> 00:05:59.567
- You been workin'?
- Yeah. No.

22
00:05:59.651 --> 00:06:01.736
Nah. Been movin' around.
you know.

23
00:06:01.820 --> 00:06:05.907
Colombia. couple of places I can't name.
Nothing catches my fancy.

24
00:06:07.784 --> 00:06:10.745
Oh.

25
00:06:10.829 --> 00:06:13.415
You think God will forgive us
for what we've done?

26
00:06:13.498 --> 00:06:16.084
- No.
- You don't?

27
00:06:16.167 --> 00:06:20.338
Me either.

28
00:06:20.463 --> 00:06:25.260
- How long you staying?
- I don't know. I just... you know.

29
00:06:25.343 --> 00:06:29.305
I wanted to see you. Ray.
see how you're doin'.

30
00:06:29.431 --> 00:06:31.933
You know. I came by on impulse.

31
00:06:32.058 --> 00:06:35.645
Well. I could do with some impulse.

32
00:06:45.739 --> 00:06:48.783
What happened?

33
00:06:48.867 --> 00:06:51.077
Family paid the ransom...

34
00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:55.165
then they sent the kid home
after a couple of days...

35
00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:57.459
minus an ear. of course.

36
00:06:57.542 --> 00:07:01.171
Now every mother in Mexico City with a little
bit of money wants bigger and better bodyguards...

37
00:07:01.296 --> 00:07:03.256
my own wife included.

38
00:07:03.340 --> 00:07:06.676
I hate to break it to you.
but she's right. She's right.

39
00:07:08.386 --> 00:07:12.640
Look. Sammy. all my clients have. uh.
kidnap and ransom insurance.

40
00:07:12.724 --> 00:07:15.977
I have a policy. A. I. G.
My dad gave it to me.

41
00:07:16.061 --> 00:07:19.356
Yeah. I know.
I got it for your dad.

42
00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:22.359
But what are you gonna do in 60 days
when you can't renew it?

43
00:07:22.484 --> 00:07:26.738
- You can't because you don't have a bodyguard.
- I had to let Emilio go.

44
00:07:26.863 --> 00:07:30.492
You gotta please Lisa.
I mean. hey. ass like that's hard to find.

45
00:07:32.911 --> 00:07:37.165
Look. a bodyguard's
like anything else.

46
00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:40.543
You get what you pay for. okay?

47
00:07:40.669 --> 00:07:43.672
You could do this.
You get one that's got a decent résumé.

48
00:07:43.755 --> 00:07:46.091
We're not looking for
goddamn Superman here. right?

49
00:07:46.216 --> 00:07:48.927
Get someone cheap
till you renew the policy...

50
00:07:49.052 --> 00:07:52.389
and then. uh...
then fire the prick for whatever.

51
00:07:52.514 --> 00:07:54.557
Incompetence.

52
00:07:54.683 --> 00:07:59.062
All kidding aside. the most important thing
is that your daughter goes back to school...

53
00:07:59.187 --> 00:08:02.148
and that your wife gets to save face.

54
00:08:02.273 --> 00:08:07.070
This way. you won't be the only
unprotected family in the neighborhood.

55
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:22.877
That's right. A bodyguard.
Your Spanish is good enough.

56
00:08:22.961 --> 00:08:26.381
- You're crazy.
- You even look the part.

57
00:08:26.464 --> 00:08:28.925
In my state.
I couldn't guard a corpse.

58
00:08:29.050 --> 00:08:31.845
It's rich guys flashing their cash.
It's all for show.

59
00:08:31.928 --> 00:08:37.058
- Nothing's gonna happen. - Yeah? You
think they'd hire a drunk. a has-been?

60
00:08:38.768 --> 00:08:42.063
You have to keep it under control.

61
00:08:42.147 --> 00:08:46.943
What if there was. you know. say.
a kidnapping attempt? What do I do then?

62
00:08:47.027 --> 00:08:51.072
You do your best. They're not gonna be
paying you enough to perform miracles.

63
00:08:51.156 --> 00:08:53.783
- I don't know.
- It's not exactly a scam. Crease.

64
00:08:53.867 --> 00:08:58.121
- Even at half speed. you're pretty damn good.
- Yeah.

65
00:08:58.204 --> 00:09:00.415
Bodyguard's gotta be close
to people though.

66
00:09:00.498 --> 00:09:03.335
He gotta talk all the time.
and I'm no good at that.

67
00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:06.963
You'll be the silent type.
People are gonna appreciate that.

68
00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:16.806
Bodyguard. So who's the guy?

69
00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:19.809
Samuel Ramos. He's a young guy.

70
00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:22.687
He owns one of the plants in Juárez.

71
00:09:22.812 --> 00:09:24.731
Yeah?

72
00:09:24.856 --> 00:09:27.651
The Jap car industry is in the toilet.

73
00:09:27.734 --> 00:09:30.695
He's trying to persuade Ford
to partner with him.

74
00:09:30.779 --> 00:09:34.658
I think he's in trouble.
His family lives in Mexico City.

75
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:37.285
He asked me if I knew
anybody he could trust.

76
00:09:38.828 --> 00:09:41.831
- And you thought of me.
- Yeah.

77
00:09:41.956 --> 00:09:45.335
Take a job. Crease.
Breathe some air.

78
00:09:45.460 --> 00:09:47.796
Then decide if you want
to stick around or not.

79
00:09:47.921 --> 00:09:52.008
Besides. I'm glad to see you.
I got nobody to talk to down here.

80
00:09:59.516 --> 00:10:02.394
Listen. my wife wants someone
presentable and polite.

81
00:10:04.771 --> 00:10:08.316
You'll be the fifth candidate
she sees this week.

82
00:10:08.400 --> 00:10:10.151
Your résumé's quite impressive.

83
00:10:10.235 --> 00:10:14.698
Sixteen years of military experience.
extensive counterterrorism work.

84
00:10:14.823 --> 00:10:18.368
I'm surprised anybody could afford you.
What's the catch?

85
00:10:18.493 --> 00:10:20.745
I drink.

86
00:10:20.870 --> 00:10:22.831
How does that affect you?

87
00:10:22.956 --> 00:10:25.417
Well...

88
00:10:25.542 --> 00:10:27.669
coordination. reaction time.

89
00:10:27.752 --> 00:10:31.506
If top professionals try to kidnap
your daughter. I'll do the best I can...

90
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:34.676
but the service will be
on par with the pay.

91
00:10:35.802 --> 00:10:37.846
What if amateurs tried?

92
00:10:37.929 --> 00:10:41.057
I'd probably kill 'em.
Is that likely?

93
00:10:41.182 --> 00:10:43.143
No.

94
00:10:43.226 --> 00:10:46.021
No one is to know about your drinking.
That includes my wife.

95
00:11:12.922 --> 00:11:15.675
-  Lisa!

96
00:11:17.886 --> 00:11:19.763
Lisa!

97
00:11:30.982 --> 00:11:33.902
My wife. Lisa.
And this is John Creasy.

98
00:11:40.950 --> 00:11:43.161
- You're an American.
- So are you.

99
00:11:45.205 --> 00:11:46.998
It's all in there.

100
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:51.961
Would you like a drink?

101
00:11:52.087 --> 00:11:54.798
Yes. uh. Jack and water'd be good.

102
00:11:56.383 --> 00:11:59.928
- Have you done much of this kind of work before?
- No. ma'am.

103
00:12:00.011 --> 00:12:03.765
But he has a lot of experience
in related fields.

104
00:12:06.309 --> 00:12:08.978
- You have a family. Mr. Creasy?
- No.

105
00:12:09.104 --> 00:12:11.314
Pita.

106
00:12:11.398 --> 00:12:13.358
Pita.

107
00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:16.778
-  Thank you.
- Yes. Mom?

108
00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:18.822
Honey. this is. uh. Mr. Creasy.

109
00:12:23.994 --> 00:12:26.454
In English. honey.

110
00:12:26.538 --> 00:12:29.165
Um. do you wanna show
Mr. Creasy to his room?

111
00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:33.003
- This way. Mr. Creasy.
- Okay.

112
00:12:41.011 --> 00:12:43.388
Thank you.

113
00:12:50.353 --> 00:12:53.148
Just like that?

114
00:12:53.231 --> 00:12:55.650
I think it's nice...

115
00:12:55.734 --> 00:12:58.236
that he's an American.

116
00:12:58.319 --> 00:13:02.532
I think it's terrific. You sure?

117
00:13:05.201 --> 00:13:07.495
Thank you.

118
00:13:07.579 --> 00:13:10.206
Thank you.

119
00:13:10.332 --> 00:13:12.792
I feel better now.

120
00:13:14.711 --> 00:13:17.589
- ¡Hola. Bruno!
- ¡Buenas tardes!

121
00:13:17.714 --> 00:13:20.008
That's Bruno. the gardener.

122
00:13:20.091 --> 00:13:22.177
And. um. that's Maria. the cook.

123
00:13:22.260 --> 00:13:25.055
- ¡Hola. Maria!
- Hola. Pita.

124
00:13:27.348 --> 00:13:31.352
We fixed the room up two weeks ago.
It's nicer than before.

125
00:13:34.564 --> 00:13:38.401
You've got a TV and C. D. Player.
What kind of music do you like. Mr. Creasy?

126
00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:40.862
I don't know.

127
00:13:40.945 --> 00:13:43.448
- You don't know?
- I don't know.

128
00:13:43.573 --> 00:13:46.743
- That's Bird.

129
00:13:46.826 --> 00:13:49.704
Emilio forgot to take him
when he left.

130
00:13:50.872 --> 00:13:53.208
Emilio was my last bodyguard.

131
00:13:55.210 --> 00:13:59.422
Have you protected a lot of children
before. Mr. Creasy?

132
00:13:59.547 --> 00:14:02.300
Creasy. You can call me Creasy.
And no. you're the first.

133
00:14:02.425 --> 00:14:04.302
Creasy.

134
00:14:04.427 --> 00:14:06.346
Bye. Creasy.

135
00:14:06.429 --> 00:14:09.099
So long.

136
00:14:10.225 --> 00:14:11.935
Bye. Bird.

137
00:14:16.606 --> 00:14:18.942
Ow.

138
00:14:21.945 --> 00:14:25.407
- School tomorrow. peeps.
- Does that mean we can get a dog?

139
00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:29.285
Dad promised me one
when I went back to school.

140
00:14:29.411 --> 00:14:31.079
Yeah. we'll see.

141
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:35.000
If you get a dog.
will you give up your bear?

142
00:14:35.125 --> 00:14:38.461
You're getting too old for him.

143
00:14:38.545 --> 00:14:41.965
- How'd you like Mr. Creasy?
- Creasy.

144
00:14:42.048 --> 00:14:44.426
He said to call him just Creasy.

145
00:14:44.509 --> 00:14:46.970
- Uh-huh.
- That isn't disrespectful. is it?

146
00:14:47.095 --> 00:14:49.389
No. not if he asked you.

147
00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:52.308
Here. There you go.

148
00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:03.945
- He's like a bear too.
- Yeah?

149
00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:06.364
A big. sad bear.

150
00:15:07.991 --> 00:15:11.619
- Is he sad?
- I think. Or something.

151
00:15:15.457 --> 00:15:17.375
- Good night. honey.
- Night.

152
00:15:20.795 --> 00:15:24.048
- Oh. can you get me some floss in the morning?
- Floss?

153
00:15:24.174 --> 00:15:27.677
- Yeah. the strawberry kind.
- Oh. sure.

154
00:15:30.055 --> 00:15:32.057
Good night. Bear.

155
00:15:33.183 --> 00:15:35.143
Creasy Bear.

156
00:16:08.676 --> 00:16:11.012
What's that one for?

157
00:16:11.096 --> 00:16:13.014
La Virgin de Guadalupe.

158
00:16:13.098 --> 00:16:17.519
Business. For Toyota. for Ford.

159
00:16:17.602 --> 00:16:20.230
If one dies. maybe she can
resurrect the other one.

160
00:16:20.355 --> 00:16:22.899
I don't know.

161
00:16:23.024 --> 00:16:25.944
- She likes him.

162
00:16:27.654 --> 00:16:30.865
- What are you talking about?
- Creasy.

163
00:16:32.409 --> 00:16:35.036
Pita likes him.

164
00:16:35.161 --> 00:16:37.080
Pita loves school.

165
00:16:37.163 --> 00:16:42.377
Pita would love Count Dracula
if he took her back there. honey.

166
00:16:42.460 --> 00:16:44.421
Okay?

167
00:16:46.923 --> 00:16:49.759
- Hey. Are you okay?
- I don't know.

168
00:16:49.884 --> 00:16:53.972
- Okay?

169
00:16:54.097 --> 00:16:56.516
I don't know. Lisa.

170
00:16:56.599 --> 00:16:58.601
I'm trying.

171
00:17:53.782 --> 00:17:55.742
Come on. Bird.

172
00:17:55.825 --> 00:17:59.204
That's right.
That's right. Come on.

173
00:17:59.329 --> 00:18:02.457
All right. Home to Emilio.

174
00:18:02.582 --> 00:18:05.460
You're home free. baby.

175
00:18:25.563 --> 00:18:28.316
- Where are you from. Creasy?
- The U. S.

176
00:18:28.441 --> 00:18:31.361
- I know. but which state?
- No state in particular.

177
00:18:31.486 --> 00:18:33.488
You can drive and talk
at the same time.

178
00:18:33.571 --> 00:18:36.032
No. I can't. Pita. so. please.
let me just do my job.

179
00:18:39.369 --> 00:18:42.205
Are you going to stay?

180
00:18:42.330 --> 00:18:44.207
My last bodyguard left.

181
00:18:44.332 --> 00:18:47.210
Somebody gave him
more money than we could.

182
00:18:47.293 --> 00:18:51.256
I guess that makes me
a bargain then. huh?

183
00:18:51.381 --> 00:18:55.760
Being black... is that a positive or negative
for a bodyguard in Mexico?

184
00:18:55.885 --> 00:18:57.762
Time will tell.

185
00:19:01.308 --> 00:19:05.562
There were 24 kidnappings
in Mexico City in the last six days.

186
00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:07.564
- Four a day.
- Yeah?

187
00:19:07.647 --> 00:19:10.108
- Twenty-four? - Twenty-four. What
do you think about that. Creasy?

188
00:19:10.233 --> 00:19:13.903
- I think that you know entirely more than you should.
- Well. thank you.

189
00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:39.638
Hola. Miguel.

190
00:19:42.182 --> 00:19:44.059
- See you later.
- You have to sign.

191
00:19:44.142 --> 00:19:48.438
- What?
- You have to sign in. show them your I. D.

192
00:19:48.563 --> 00:19:51.983
Buenos días. Come on.

193
00:19:53.151 --> 00:19:55.070
Right there.

194
00:19:55.153 --> 00:19:57.781
- Hola. Manuel.
- Hola. Pita.

195
00:20:08.583 --> 00:20:10.460
- ¡Hola. Pita!
- ¡Hola!

196
00:20:10.585 --> 00:20:14.756
Pita! It's so good to have you back.

197
00:20:14.881 --> 00:20:17.801
Sister Anna. this is
my new bodyguard. Creasy.

198
00:20:17.884 --> 00:20:21.012
Sister Anna. the headmistress.

199
00:20:21.137 --> 00:20:23.139
- Señor Creasy.

200
00:20:23.264 --> 00:20:25.141
Hurry. Class is about to begin.

201
00:20:25.266 --> 00:20:27.602
- Go. go.
- Bye. Creasy.

202
00:20:27.686 --> 00:20:30.188
- Madre.
- You must look after our Pita.

203
00:20:30.313 --> 00:20:32.482
It is not good that she's late today.

204
00:20:32.607 --> 00:20:37.153
I'm very sorry. I. uh... I'll have to get
used to the rules. It won't happen again.

205
00:20:37.278 --> 00:20:40.824
No offense. but I regret
that your profession needs to exist.

206
00:20:40.949 --> 00:20:44.077
So do I. Madre.  So do I.

207
00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:48.123
Do you ever see the hand of God
in what you do?

208
00:20:49.749 --> 00:20:51.876
No. not for a long time.

209
00:20:52.002 --> 00:20:55.338
The Bible says.
"Be not overcome of evil. but overcome... "

210
00:20:55.463 --> 00:20:58.883
"Overcome evil with good. "

211
00:21:05.056 --> 00:21:07.851
I'm the sheep that got lost. Madre.

212
00:22:11.247 --> 00:22:14.292
When you were a kid. Creasy.
did you like school?

213
00:22:15.877 --> 00:22:18.046
- I don't remember.
- You don't remember?

214
00:22:18.171 --> 00:22:22.092
No. I don't remember.
It. uh... Nah. I didn't like it.

215
00:22:22.175 --> 00:22:24.219
Why not?

216
00:22:24.344 --> 00:22:26.888
Because it wasn't a school like yours.

217
00:22:27.013 --> 00:22:28.974
There was no. uh... no Sister Anna.

218
00:22:31.893 --> 00:22:34.020
Were you unhappy?

219
00:22:36.231 --> 00:22:39.609
Being unhappy. Pita. that's a state of mind.
I really don't remember.

220
00:22:49.077 --> 00:22:51.162
What happened to your hand?

221
00:22:52.705 --> 00:22:54.624
- It's a birth defect.
- No. it's not.

222
00:22:54.708 --> 00:22:58.962
- Look. no more questions. okay?

223
00:22:59.087 --> 00:23:01.464
- It really wasn't a question.
- It sounded like a question.

224
00:23:01.548 --> 00:23:04.134
Look. I got a job to do. Hey!

225
00:23:04.259 --> 00:23:06.469
No. Gracias. Gracias.  No. No.

226
00:23:06.594 --> 00:23:09.514
Listen to me.
I'm being paid to protect you. okay?

227
00:23:09.639 --> 00:23:12.600
No. no. no. I'm being paid
to be your bodyguard.

228
00:23:12.684 --> 00:23:15.770
Look at me.
I'm not being paid to be your friend.

229
00:23:15.895 --> 00:23:19.441
I'm being paid to protect you.
so no more questions. That's it. Period.

230
00:23:23.278 --> 00:23:25.947
- You hear me?
- Yes.

231
00:23:26.072 --> 00:23:29.492
- And no crying.
- I'm not crying.

232
00:23:29.617 --> 00:23:32.662
- Well. don't start.

233
00:23:32.787 --> 00:23:35.206
You gotta understand. this is a job.

234
00:23:35.332 --> 00:23:38.126
- In order for me to do...

235
00:23:38.209 --> 00:23:40.170
In order for... Wait a minute.

236
00:24:29.803 --> 00:24:31.763
Yeah. come in.

237
00:24:37.393 --> 00:24:39.521
Mr. Creasy.

238
00:24:39.646 --> 00:24:42.440
I just wanted to make sure
you have everything you need.

239
00:24:42.565 --> 00:24:44.526
I'm fine. thanks.

240
00:24:46.611 --> 00:24:49.948
Is the food all right?
'Cause. uh. Maria told me you didn't eat.

241
00:24:50.073 --> 00:24:53.535
Uh... yeah. the food is great.

242
00:24:53.618 --> 00:24:56.121
I just wasn't that hungry tonight.

243
00:24:59.499 --> 00:25:02.085
